# Documentation Rules

## When to Document

- After feature completion
- After code changes that affect behavior
- When documentation is explicitly requested

## Documentation Types

### Full Generation (init-docs)
1. Read project root files to identify project type and tech stack
2. Scan source directories to map architecture
3. Create `docs/` directory structure:
   - `docs/README.md` — main table of contents
   - `docs/architecture/` — system design
   - `docs/api/` — API documentation
   - `docs/guides/` — how-to guides
   - `docs/reference/` — configuration and reference
4. Build navigation with cross-references

### Incremental Update (update-docs)
1. Run `git diff --name-only HEAD~10` to identify recently changed files
2. Determine which existing docs are affected
3. Update affected documents, add new sections, remove obsolete content
4. Verify cross-links and table of contents

## Standards

- **File naming:** kebab-case (`user-authentication.md`)
- **Structure:** Title → Overview → Main sections → Examples → Related Documents
- **Writing:** Clear, concise, practical examples, explain "why" not just "what"
- **Cross-linking:** Relative paths, bidirectional links, update on moves/renames
